---
import LegalLayout from '@/layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  locale="en"
  pathname="/privacy"
  title="Privacy Policy"
  metaDescription="What DailyMood collects, what we do with it, and your rights under Thailand PDPA — written plain. No data selling, no hidden trackers."
  effectiveDate="Effective May 17, 2026"
  tldr={[
    'We only collect what we need to run DailyMood.',
    'Your entries are yours — we never sell or share them.',
    'We use Google Analytics for traffic stats (only after you consent). No ad cookies.',
    'You can access, edit, export, or delete your data anytime.',
  ]}
>
  <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
  <p>When you sign up and use DailyMood, we collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Account info:</strong> your email, display name, password
      (stored so we can't read it — only you know it), and any OAuth
      profile data if you sign in with Google.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Mood entries:</strong> the mood you choose, notes you type,
      tags, photos (if you upload any), and the date/time.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>AI usage:</strong> how many AI calls you make per day, used
      to enforce rate limits.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Payments:</strong> if you subscribe to Pro, we store a Stripe
      customer ID only — we never see your card number. Stripe handles that.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How we use AI</h2>
  <p>
    When you use AI-powered features (entry summary, photo analysis, Ask AI),
    we send your text or image to an external AI provider (currently Google)
    for stateless processing — your entries are not retained by the AI
    provider, and they are never used to train any AI model.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Images</h2>
  <p>
    If you upload a photo, we store it on Cloudflare R2 and serve it via
    signed URLs that expire within 1 hour. Your photos are never publicly
    accessible — only you can view them.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> to understand how people
    use our site (which pages are visited most, which browsers people use,
    etc.). We don't identify individuals. Google Analytics
    <strong>only runs after you click "Accept all"</strong> on the cookie
    banner — see <a href="/en/cookies">Cookie Policy</a> for details.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
  <p>We rely on the following providers to run DailyMood:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Google</strong> — OAuth for login, AI models for AI features, and Google Analytics for traffic stats.</li>
    <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing for Pro.</li>
    <li><strong>Resend</strong> — transactional email (verification, password reset).</li>
    <li><strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — image and avatar storage.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud hosting provider</strong> — runs our app and database.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Each provider has its own privacy policy. Your data may be transferred
    outside Thailand depending on where these services operate.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep your data as long as your account is active. If you delete your
    account, we remove all your entries and images within 30 days, except
    data we're required to retain by law (e.g., payment receipts).
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your rights under PDPA</h2>
  <p>
    Under Thailand's Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA) B.E. 2562, you
    have the right to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access and request a copy of your data</li>
    <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
    <li>Request deletion</li>
    <li>Restrict or object to processing</li>
    <li>Export your data (data portability)</li>
    <li>Withdraw consent</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Send rights requests to
    <a href="mailto:hello@dailymood.me">hello@dailymood.me</a>. We respond
    within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about privacy or your data? Reach us at
    <a href="mailto:hello@dailymood.me">hello@dailymood.me</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
